bcl:definition.bcl:text:
adopted provision means a provision adopted under section 9
(1) and, if changed under section 9 (2) (a), means the provision as changed under
that section;

railway company means a company that has received an
authorization under section 3 of the Railway
  Act;

  applicable provisions means the provisions of the preceding
Act and of the regulations made under that Act that were applicable to a railway company
with an authorization;
